        <p style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.7;color:#555;margin:0;">Swapping out an undersized or aging basement window for a code-compliant egress unit, common in Hickman homes built before the city's biggest growth years.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:10px;padding:26px;box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(14,77,110,0.05);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 8px;">Window Well Installation</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.7;color:#555;margin:0;">Properly sized wells with drainage built for Lancaster County soil and weather, keeping newer Hickman basements dry through spring and summer storms.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:10px;padding:26px;box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(14,77,110,0.05);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 8px;">Basement Window Replacement</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.7;color:#555;margin:0;">Upgrading standard basement windows to egress-ready openings as growing Hickman families finish out basement space for kids' bedrooms or guest rooms.</p>
