<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Why Egress Windows Matter for Hickman's New Construction</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>Hickman has been one of the fastest-growing small cities in Lancaster County, and most of that growth is homes built in the 2000s and later with big, open basements. Builders often leave that space unfinished, which means the egress window may not have been part of the original build if the basement wasn't planned as living space from day one.</p><p>If you're finishing that basement now for a bedroom, home office, or extra living area, an egress window isn't optional. It's the difference between a room that's just storage and one that's a legal, sellable bedroom.</p><p>We handle the full <a href="/egress-window-installation-lincoln/">egress window installation</a> process for Hickman homes, from the initial cut to a finished, code-compliant opening.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Serving Hickman and the Norris School District Area</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>Hickman sits just south of Lincoln and draws families in for the Norris School District, which has pulled a steady stream of new residential construction into the area. That growth has made Hickman one of the more active markets in Lancaster County for basement finishing projects.</p><p>We're familiar with the mix of home styles across Hickman, from newer subdivisions to older homes closer to the city's historic core, and we size every egress window and window well to the specific home rather than a one-size-fits-all approach.</p><p>Whether you're in a brand-new build or an older Hickman home, we can walk your basement and give you a clear picture of what a compliant egress opening will take. See our <a href="/egress-window-cost/">egress window cost</a> page for typical pricing ranges.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Window Wells Built for Nebraska Weather</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>A new egress window is only as good as the window well around it. Poor drainage or an undersized well leads to water sitting against the foundation, which is a real risk during Nebraska's heavier spring rains.</p><p>We build every <a href="/window-well-installation-lincoln/">window well</a> to drain properly and hold up to freeze-thaw cycles, so Hickman homeowners aren't dealing with a flooded well or a cracked cover a few years down the road.</p><p>If you're not sure whether your current window well is doing its job, we're happy to take a look and give you a straight answer, no pressure.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:72px 24px;background:#EAF5FB;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="kicker">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(24px,3.5vw,36px);margin:0 0 32px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Do older homes in Hickman need egress windows too, or is this just for new construction?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Any basement being finished as a bedroom needs a compliant egress window, regardless of when the home was built. Hickman has a mix of older homes near the city center and newer construction from the recent growth years, and we install and retrofit egress windows in both.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">How long does egress window installation take for a typical Hickman basement?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Most single-window installations take one to two days depending on foundation type and whether we're cutting into poured concrete or block. Newer Hickman homes with standard basement layouts are usually on the faster end, while older foundations can take a bit longer.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Will an egress window help if I'm planning to sell my Hickman home?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Yes. A basement bedroom without a legal egress window can hold up a sale or come up as a red flag during inspection. Given how many buyers are looking at Hickman right now, having that basement bedroom already code-compliant is a real advantage.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Can you match the egress window to my home's existing style?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Yes, we install a range of egress window styles and frame materials, and we'll help you pick an option that fits your home's exterior. We'll also confirm the well cover and grading work with your yard's slope, which varies across Hickman's different neighborhoods.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
